            <mxPoint x="399.13" y="272" as="targetPoint" />
          </mxGeometry>
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="aIY0HfDJ9va3LicR7WyO-30" value="&lt;h1&gt;Onboarding &amp;amp; Certificate Issuance Process&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;1. Certcheck Admin invites the university on the portal. The invitation email will be sent to the university user with the invitation code. Using the Invitation code, the user from the university can register and log in to the portal.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;2. Once registered and logged in to the portal, the university user can upload the certificate and assign it to the candidate&lt;/p&gt;&lt;blockquote style=&quot;margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;2.1. The university can use its own database and link it with the Certcheck portal where uploaded data will be added to the hyperledger network and the HASH is created through the CertCheck Blockchain Engine.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;2.2. The university can opt for CertCheck database, where it will be configured for the respective university and they can begin with the upload process.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: initial;&quot;&gt;3. When the Certificate is uploaded, it will be assigned to the candidate. The candidate will receive an email notification for the uploaded certificate.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;4. Candidate can register on the platform if not part of CertCheck or log in to the portal to claim the certificate. The candidate account will present the list of all certificates assigned by the university.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;spacing=5;spacingTop=-20;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="87.63" y="600" width="699" height="290" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
  <diagram name="Copy of CertCheck-Onboarding" id="A8oKL7NZlgjYQzEfAHo9">
    <mxGraphModel grid="1" page="1" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" pageScale="1" pageWidth="850" pageHeight="1100" math="0" shadow="0">
      <root>
        <mxCell id="YMe9DCUnE6XLKINWfvn1-0" />
        <mxCell id="YMe9DCUnE6XLKINWfvn1-1" parent="YMe9DCUnE6XLKINWfvn1-0" />
        <mxCell id="YMe9DCUnE6XLKINWfvn1-33" value="&lt;h1&gt;Onboarding &amp;amp; Certificate Issuance Process&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;1. Certcheck Admin invites the university on the portal. The invitation email will be sent to the university user with the invitation code. Using the Invitation code, the user from the university can register and log in to the portal.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;2. Once registered and logged in to the portal, the university user can upload the certificate and assign it to the candidate&lt;/p&gt;&lt;blockquote style=&quot;margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;2.1. The university can use its own database and link it with the Certcheck portal where uploaded data will be added to the hyperledger network and the HASH is created through the CertCheck Blockchain Engine.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;2.2. The university can opt for CertCheck database, where it will be configured for the respective university and they can begin with the upload process.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: initial;&quot;&gt;3. When the Certificate is uploaded, it will be assigned to the candidate. The candidate will receive an email notification for the uploaded certificate.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;4. Candidate can register on the platform if not part of CertCheck or log in to the portal to claim the certificate. The candidate account will present the list of all certificates assigned by the university.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;spacing=5;spacingTop=-20;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" parent="YMe9DCUnE6XLKINWfvn1-1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="87.63" y="600" width="699" height="290" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
