        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="53qRH_ZbhQs-7e9-ppgg-32" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=0;orthogonalLoop=1;jettySize=auto;html=1;exitX=0.97;exitY=0.5;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;exitPerimeter=0;" edge="1" parent="53qRH_ZbhQs-7e9-ppgg-1" source="53qRH_ZbhQs-7e9-ppgg-2">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry">
            <mxPoint x="399.13" y="272" as="targetPoint" />
          </mxGeometry>
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="53qRH_ZbhQs-7e9-ppgg-33" value="&lt;h1&gt;HASH VERIFICATION PROCESS BY VERIFIER&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;1. The candidate will share the HASH with the verifier (OFFLINE). Verifer will come to the portal and put a search request on the certcheck portal. The candidate will receive a notification to allow the verifier to view the information that belongs to the HASH.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;2. The candidate will log in to the portal to check the request and validate the user who has requested. Once consent is given by the candidate, CertCheck will trigger the university database to get the data for the given HASH&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;3. Certcheck will fetch the information and validate it on the blockchain network for the HASH and university data.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;4. Once the data is matched, CertCheck platform will share the information with the verifier&lt;/p&gt;" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;spacing=5;spacingTop=-20;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="53qRH_ZbhQs-7e9-ppgg-1">
          <mxGeometry x="87.63" y="600" width="699" height="190" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
